headline: Why Intel Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Intel (NASDAQ: INTC) stock price was down by 2.9% as of 3 p.m. ET Monday, even as the S&P 500 index was up by 0.5% and the Nasdaq Composite had gained 1% for the day.  The chipmaker's decline appears to be linked to an article published late Friday by The Wall Street Journal that highlighted the challenges facing the company.  Is Intel getting left in the dust?
